parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition System Failure to Turn Off
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system to turn off can cause the battery to drain, leading to stranding, and potentially result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: but the radio and accessories remain on
the car requires multiple attempts to turn off
the car stays on even after pressing the start/stop button

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter position switch can cause the vehicle to not turn off completely, leading to battery drain and potential safety risks.
symptoms: the vehicle does not recognize it is in park
the vehicle will not shut off when the start button is pressed
the vehicle requires multiple attempts to turn off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected cracking of the windshield can cause a loss of visibility, leading to accidents, and potentially injure the driver and passengers.
symptoms: without any apparent impact or debris
often starting from the center or edge of the windshield and spreading horizontally or vertically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, startle the driver, and potentially injure the driver and passengers with flying glass.
symptoms: without any apparent impact or debris
and produces a loud explosion-like sound.
